                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.516/116</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Parker</persName>, representing
                        American interests, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-14T16:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>228. Department’s 198, December 28, 6 p.m. Minister of Finance has just replied
                    that in order to give the proper answer to the suggestions contained in said
                    telegram it will be necessary for the Department to refer to concrete cases of
                    proposed drastic measures <pb facs="0709" n="633" xml:id="pg_633"/> as so far
                    the Government has only issued a decree by which banks of issue are required to
                    comply with provisions of banking laws which were in existence when the
                    revolution began.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Parker</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
